<Content>Charming and Affordable in Beverly Hills, but needs some improvement We found this hotel on Trip Advisor while searching for something affordable but charming in Beverly Hills. Hard to find such a combo in this area, and the affordable is relative to the area. Like the 60s retro feeeling combined with the nouveau decor. Loved the big balcony and the view of Hollywood Hills. Could even see the famous Hollywood on the hill faraway fromthe balcony. The hotel room was very beautiful and peaceful and spacious. But NO Tempur-Pedic bed in THIS room (#606), to our disappoinment since we had really looked forward to that when we saw they advertised having them in all rooms! The public areas of the hotel were well designed and alluring.Could make this hotel a destination in itself: restaurant, room service, pool, live entertainment some nights, pool table, Beverly Hils nearby, comfortable sitting areas off lobby. Great restaurant next door too: Sparks. Had to wait a long while to check in to hotel - very slow. Hotel room was, however, not at all quiet: we could hear doors slamming, voices, vacuum cleaners all from our bed. As long as our neighboring guests were quiet our room was too. The AC fan did not work - so there was no way to block the noises and also no way to cool off the room without opening the glass doors, which then allowed in more noise from the street. SO this place is a mixed bag: lots of new, a little 60s; great service at valet and concierge, slow at front desk; noisy at times, quiet at others, beautiful lobby and lounging areas. Overall, FEELS good to be there though. Felt like a nice respite from all the traffic we had to drive in to get there, where we could sit back and relax. 
