<Content>Stylish,good value and location First time for an extended stay in LA and the location was excellent for sightseeing around Beverly Hills, Hollywood and even downtown was not too far by car. We had very helpful tips from the Stephen the Concierge about getting around without going on the freeways and sightseeing, for example he recommended the Kodak Theatre tour as worthwhile which it was amongst the tackiness of Hollywod Boulevard (The city is working on it but still has a way to go).The room was spacious, clean and had very original and smart decoration. We had a very good rate through Expedia but we decided to upgrade to a north view towards Beverly Hills and itwas well worth it, as the view from the quite large balcony was very pretty and green ( for LA!).The bathroom was spacious enough for 2 adults and 2 teenagers, as there is a separate area with a dressing table and mirror (also where the coffee machine was located), so everyone had a place to put their 'things''. The bathroom probably could do with a makeover soon as there was a hairline crack in the basin, and the toilet was a bit temperamental but otherwise everything was fine and they even had a heated shaving mirror.The bedding was divine ( Tempur matresses). Sensibly the hotel has ditched the mini bar service which I am sure no one uses these days which left plenty of space in the small fridge for our drinks and snacks.All th staff were friendly and professional from the front door to the restaurant. Housekeeping when asked quickly replaced items they had missed ie decaf coffee. We had dinner twice in the restaurant. The menu is small but covered most tastes and we found the food to be good and reasonable in price.Parking is an issue around Beverly Hills ( ie parking on the street is not allowed) so the valet charge is unavoidable but the service is very convenient.Don't be put off by the exterior ( it has a 60's almost retro look) but inside it it very smart, intimate and welcoming. 
