<Author>Jerri_Blank
<Content>Needs Improvement I stayed in two different types of room over one night, a one-bedroom, and a single. So Ive seen what they have to offer. Here's the negatives:1) The reviews are true, the decor is tired and stained. Lot's of floral print and striped patters, so maybe some people don't notice the stains? I saw stains all over the place.2) Sheets/pillowcases also had stains, although they were clean in my first room, the one-bedroom.3) I asked for a rollaway bed in the early afternoon. They said it'd be right up. Around 10pm it still wasn't there. When I called, I was informed that they were out. See positve item #1 below...4) When I moved to the single, there was a unidentifiable smell. They had also left an Air Deodorizer machine in the room. I decided to turn that on an open the balcony doors. After a while I noticed that the label on the machine said that it releases ozone, and can should not be used withh people in the room, so I turned it off and opened the doors all the way. The room still smelled and now I was worried about getting sick, so I slept with the doors all the way open. Luckily it was a holiday, so not a lot of traffic.5) Jacuzzi tub in one-bedroom suite very small, and didn't work.6) Single room doesn't have a jacuzzi tub.7) Valet only parking for $22. They park it right there!8) TV in single room didn't work.Now the positives:1) Cathy at the front desk is awesome. Extremely helpful. When I called to ask about the rollaway not showing up, she gave me a free separate room. She is the only reason I'm giving this hotel more than 1 point.2) The decor in the single was slightly better, and a bit cleaner. Only a few stains, and just one piece of trash left over on the floor from the last guest.3) Balconies were small, but nice. The rooms I had had a good view. Other reviews mentioned a view of the Hollywood sign - not true. On the 10th floor, there's a VIP lounge, there you can see most directions. It is not possible to see the Hollywood sign from this hotel.4) Bed was comfortable, except I did sleep in jeans and a shirt because I was afraid of the stained sheets.5) I didn't try the restaurant, but it looked nice.6) The workout room and pool seem to be in great condition, but I didn't use them.Other Loews that I've stayed at, I've always thought they were luxurious. This was very disappointing. They really need to remodel, I won't stay here again until they fix their problems. 
