<Content>I Love This Place! Stayed here for one night on December 26, 2005. Got a very good price on the Loew's website. It's a boutique hotel run by a large chain. The staff couldn't have been nicer - from the valet parking attendent, the doorman and everyone we dealt with at the front desk. We had a lovely room, very well appointed with free Wi-Fi, lovely terrace with a view and a very, very comfortable bed. The room was immaculate and the hotel had a very cozy feel to it. It's located on the edge of a beautiful residential area, which sets it apart from most of the other hotels I've stayed at in LA. They keep excellent computerized records of their return guests, so when you check in, they know if you like a particular view, etc. I was impressed. Skip the continental breakfast, which is fine though, and take a 10 minute stroll down Beverwil to Urth Cafe for the best cappuccino and pastries that I've found in LA. 
